IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Case Type: 1st Degree Assault Location: 10507 River Rd, Denton, Caroline County, Maryland, 21629 Date and Time of Incident: 10/28/2023 0012 hours Attachments: Chain of Custody/Property Held Linda Wright Written Statement Nathan Wright Written Statement Domestic Violence Supplement Charging Documents Gun Center Report Emergency Petition Photographs Body Camera Footage: Footage was captured on TFC Emberts, and TFC Elmores body Camera footage. Narrative: On October 28th, 2023 at approximately 0012 hours, I TFC Embert along with other members of the Maryland State Police, were dispatched to 10507 River Rd, Denton for a physical domestic dispute. The call was reported by a third party who was identified as Nathan Wright. Nathan stated that his father, James Wright, and his stepmother, Kelly Bartin, had been involved in a physical domestic. Nathan reported that Bartin had already left the River Rd address and was now located at 111 10th St in Denton. Denton Police department responded to that address to check Bartins welfare. While still en route, another party who was identified at Skylar Breeding, contacted the barrack. She stated that James had called her and was very upset and crying. Skylar stated that James said that he was going to blow his head off. Linda Wright, who is James mother and also lives at the River Rd address but in a separate residence, contacted the barrack and stated that James was outside shooting. She advised he was somewhere around the chicken house (where James resides). Linda also stated that James was very emotional and not thinking clearly. She also stated that James has access to multiple firearms. Due to the nature of the incident, responding units staged down the road to establish a plan to approach the suspect in the safest manner. Four (4) Maryland State Police Units, three (3) Caroline County Sheriffs Office units, and one (1) Denton Police Department K-9 unit where gathered on River Rd. While these units were staged, TFC Capranica of the Maryland State Police responded to the 111 10th St address and made contact with Kelly. TFC Capranica will be completing a supplemental report detailing the altercation that occurred between Kelly and James SGT Stivers of the Caroline County Sheriffs Office was equipped with a drone with thermal capabilities. This device was utilized in an attempt to locate James location on the property. SGT Stivers was able to observe a golf cart leave the chicken house and drive to the other residence on the property. When this happened, The units staged on River Rd responded to the River Rd address and took James into custody without incident. James stated that he didnt know why we were there and that he was not suicidal. James gave permission to myself and the other units on scene to enter his residence and retrieve the shotgun he was shooting. The shotgun was identified as a Mossberg Model 88 12 Gauge and was seized. During this, it was also discovered that James had shot the windshield of a Ford F150 on the property the vehicle which displayed Maryland registration 7EL8323. The vehicle is registered to Kelly. During the investigation, Nathan arrived at the house. Nathan stated that his father had called him earlier in the night, telling him Kelly had left because they had a fight. Nathan then called Kelly, and she told him that James had choked her and thrown her into the wall and the floor. Nathan stated he then called 911 to report the domestic assault. James later called Nathan again and told him he fucked up. Nathan provided a written statement that is attached to this report. I spoke to Linda who stated that earlier in the night James and Kelly were at her house and everything seemed fine. She stated that she didnt know what was going on until Nathan called her. Linda provided a written statement that is attached to this report. I was able to see video from James ring camera. This footage showed him standing outside in a robe and shooting a shotgun into the air multiple times. He makes the comment is this loaded and then pulls the trigger. The gun fires and James loads more shells into the magazine tube. I was able to get a copy of this video. During the investigation the Maryland Gun Center was contacted. It was discovered that James was prohibited and disqualified from possessing firearms and ammunition. Due to this, Linda took possession of all of James non regulated firearms and placed them in a safe that James did not have access to. Linda was informed that James is not allowed to regain possession of firearms. The regulated firearms that James posed were taken and processed at the Maryland State Police Easton Barrack. The Remington Model 870 was also seized. All firearms are listed in the firearms section of this report. Also seized was eight (8) empty 12 gauge shot shells and two (2) live 12 gauge shot shells. These shot shells where located outside if the chicken house on the ground. James was taken to Easton Hospital for an Emergency Petition and was later released. While I was transporting James to the Caroline County Commissioner, James stated that he wanted to talk about what happened. James stated that he did not remember much of the details but did not remember assaulting Kelly. He stated that he did remember shooting the windshield of the truck. James also stated that he did not remember going to the hospital. James was transported to the Commissioner where he was held without bond. All events occurred in Caroline County Maryland. I request this case remain open pending a supplement from TFC Capranica.

On November 1, 2023, at approximately 1316 hours, I completed a domestic violence follow-up with Bartin via telephone. Bartin advised she did not wish to pursue a protective order at this time and did not have new signs of injury. She further advised that she had the contact information fo Mid-Shore Family Council. This case remains closed.

NARRATIVE: On November 7, 2023, investigators of the Firearms Enforcement Unit (FEU) were contacted by the Detective Sergeant of the Easton Barrack I to perform a test fire on two seized handguns. Investigators conducted test fires on the following handguns: Make: Bond Arms Model: Snake Slayer Caliber: 45 Colt Serial Number: 39039 and Make: Smith Wesson Model: 629 Classic Caliber: 44 Mag Serial Number: DAP5716. The test fires were conducted utilizing the Forensic Buddy which is a Portable Bullet Recovery System for Ballistic Comparison. Investigators fired two rounds of 45 Colt caliber and 44 Mag ammunition. The firearms were found to be functional and in working order. For both handguns, the shell casings and projectiles were collected, packaged, and processed per Maryland State Police policy. Both the shell casings and projectiles were sent to the Maryland State Police Forensic Division to be entered into the National Integrated Ballistic Information Network (NIBIN). All events occurred in Easton County, Maryland. Case Closed.

This incident was captured on camera. partner_id=5ed6a168304e40eb9a0cfb1a226ef1a1" target="_blank">BODY CAM NARRATIVE: On 10/28/23, at approximately 0050 hours, I, TFC Capranica #6564, with the Maryland State Police Easton Barrack, responded to the residence of 111 10th St, to contact the victim, Kelly Bartin. Denton PD had already contacted Bartin, prior to my arrival, to check her welfare. Bartin advised Denton PD Officers, Wright attempted to strangle her, but she was okay and did not need medical treatment and refused EMS. Bartin sat in my patrol car, while I questioned her about the incident. Bartin was visibly upset and frightened by the event that had occurred between her and Wright. I advised her that Wright had just been arrested, which gave her some relief. Bartin advised Wright was highly intoxicated. Bartin trying to lay down in the bed and sleep, and Wright came in and kicked her out of the bed onto the cement floor. I asked Bartin to describe how Wright strangled her. Bartin explained that Wright put both his hands around her neck, while she was in the bed. She then tried to get out of the bed, and Wright grabbed her by the throat again. I asked Bartin how long she thought his hands were around her neck, and she stated, Not long, I was trying to get away. I asked her if she remembered having trouble breathing, and she stated, I think there was a moment I was worried about breathing. I observed physical signs of injury to Bartins neck. On the right side of her neck, I observed a red mark and abrasion. I took photos of the injuries and sent then to TFC Embert. She then showed me Ring camera recordings of Wright going outside and shooting a shotgun into the air, several times. Bartin emailed me the clips, which I then forwarded to Cpl. Bringman. All events occurred in Caroline Co.
